1
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,880
We finally meet.

2
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:08,360
I've been wondering.

3
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:11,360
How did I offend you?

4
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:13,880
You can tell me.

5
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,440
If I really offended you,

6
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:18,480
I am willing to apologize to you.

7
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:21,080
You do have a lot of people to apologize to,

8
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,640
but I am not one of them.

9
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:27,160
And your problem cannot be solved just by apologizing.

10
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:34,380
Let's not talk about whether it can be solved or not.

11
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:39,100
Since you said I don't need to apologize,

12
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:41,640
why do you keep targeting me?

13
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,320
At first,

14
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:44,840
I had no choice.

15
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,880
Later, after I found out what you did,

16
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:52,200
I had even less of a choice.

17
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,860
You are not young anymore.

18
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,250
Why are you so childish?

19
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:14,400
Do you really think you're some kind of superhero?

20
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:17,160
You said it yourself.

21
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,810
We don't have any direct conflict.

22
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:21,980
How about this?

23
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,690
You give me the flash drive,

24
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,760
and I'll let bygones be bygones.

25
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,000
You've lost your job as a cop,

26
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,360
and your career has hit a wall.

27
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,000
Work for me from now on.

28
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,320
Whatever you want,

29
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,800
I can give it to you.

30
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,600
In my current situation,

31
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,800
hearing you say that,

32
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,320
makes me really want to take your offer.

33
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:51,440
But the flash drive really isn't in my hands.

34
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,760
That's strange.

35
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:06,160
Who exactly is lying?

36
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,600
Those three women said

37
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,960
you have it.

38
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,960
You're listening to them?

39
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,400
Those three bitches.

40
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,480
After I helped them,

41
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,680
they actually turned around and bit me.

42
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,900
This little act of infighting

43
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,680
isn't very convincing.

44
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,040
You can tell?

45
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:32,040
I guess I'll have to work on my acting skills.

46
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:37,280
You don't really think

47
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:40,890
you can take me down with this flash drive, do you?

48
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:52,880
All the bribery and shady deals on that drive

49
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:55,680
have long been risk-proofed by me.

50
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,800
I had other people act as the front.

51
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,400
Even if you release all of this,

52
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,660
the ones who will really suffer are them.

53
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:10,040
It won't hurt me one bit.

54
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,490
Will it really not hurt you?

55
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,480
If all those people go down,

56
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:18,440
won't the protective umbrella you've worked so hard to build over the years

57
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,000
collapse entirely?

58
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,440
A slight change in the weather

59
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:22,640
and a little rain,

60
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,600
could still get you wet.

61
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,640
If it rains harder,

62
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,240
it might just crush you to death.

63
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,040
Okay.

64
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:47,200
Then let's see

65
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,860
how you're going to change the weather in Tangzhou.

66
00:04:55,159 --> 00:04:56,320
I'll take a rest.

67
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:58,580
You get some exercise.

68
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,160
Pretty tough, huh?

69
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,240
Then feed him some more.

70
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,800
I'll go take care of those women.

71
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,000
Don't go.

72
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,920
Let's talk man to man.

73
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:26,210
What else is there to eat and drink?

74
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:27,720
Bring it on.

75
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,680
There is.

76
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:30,400
Want a beer?

77
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:33,180
But there are two ways to drink it.

78
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,120
One is a toast,

79
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,780
and the other is a penalty.

80
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:41,480
I've always been a glutton for punishment.

81
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:42,900
I can't handle a toast.

82
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:46,200
Let me see what this penalty drink is all about.

83
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,240
How does it taste?

84
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:24,810
It's delicious.

85
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:27,360
You must try it if you get the chance.

86
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,000
I always thought

87
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,560
our romance was fleeting

88
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:50,760
and we would never see each other again.

89
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,360
I didn't expect you to miss me so much.

90
00:07:54,159 --> 00:07:55,880
After what you did to us,

91
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,440
how could we forget?

92
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,280
Not only will we not forget,

93
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,010
but we won't let you off either.

94
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:02,960
Typical women.

95
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:06,000
But I'm different.

96
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,000
I'm very generous.

97
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:12,970
If you three just tell me where the flash drive is,

98
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:16,160
I will let you go.

99
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:26,560
We won't tell.

100
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,040
I guessed as much.

101
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,520
Fine.

102
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:38,980
Forget it if you don't want to tell me.

103
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:33,360
What's wrong?

104
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,200
Do you feel sorry for her?

105
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:39,920
Mute girl.

106
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:45,800
Oh, right.

107
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,640
I forgot you can't speak.

108
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:53,840
I participated in a disabled assistance event a few days ago.

109
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,650
I even became an ambassador for the disabled.

110
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,120
So,

111
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,880
I can't just talk the talk.

112
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,800
I need to take some real action.

113
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,880
I'll spare you for now.

114
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,360
Jessica.

115
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,480
Let me tell you,

116
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:25,000
I missed you the most out of the three of you.

117
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:27,600
Really.

118
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:30,760
If

119
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:35,960
Lawyer An hadn't kept stopping me back then,

120
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:39,880
I would have definitely kept you by my side forever.

121
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,520
I didn't expect you to come back on your own.

122
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,400
Then the two of us

123
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,880
should catch up properly.

124
00:10:58,680 --> 00:10:59,640
Don't touch her.

125
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:00,960
Don't touch her.

126
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:02,640
Wait a minute.

127
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:11,840
We really don't know where it is.

128
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:13,480
Shao Yu took the stuff.

129
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,680
Are you playing with me?

130
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,440
You won't tell me, right?

131
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,360
I get it.

132
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:00,920
You are intentionally stalling for time, aren't you?

133
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,280
What's wrong?

134
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,760
Do you have other plans?

135
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,160
Let me tell you,

136
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:11,120
no matter what other plans you have,

137
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,120
they are useless.

138
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:18,160
I've suddenly decided too.

139
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:21,020
I don't think it's necessary to keep so many people.

140
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,210
Keeping one who can talk is enough.

141
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,480
But to be honest,

142
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:40,120
I really can't bear to part with you three.

143
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,560
Then let's start

144
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,480
with that kid named Shao.

145
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,320
I told you to drink properly just now, but you didn't.

146
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,280
No more chances.

147
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,760
Pull yourselves together.

148
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:02,160
Prepare to be on your way.

149
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,920
In less than two hours,

150
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:08,800
he will say goodbye to you for good.

151
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,440
It's fine.

152
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,170
There's still a way.

153
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:18,180
If you really value your friendship with him

154
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,410
and want to save him,

155
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:23,600
you can tell me anytime within two hours.

156
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:30,040
But if his death means nothing to you,

157
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,400
that's fine too.

158
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:36,200
After he dies,

159
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:40,650
you three can take the opportunity to discuss

160
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,480
who will be next.

161
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,440
Karma sure comes fast.

162
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:11,920
Yeah.

163
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:14,260
So you guys should be careful too.

164
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:18,020
You are the most stubborn guy I've ever seen.

165
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:20,800
But once this cement is poured over you,

166
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:24,380
your attitude won't be the only thing that's hardened.

167
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:27,360
There are about 15 standards for concrete.

168
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,040
But we aren't building roads or bridges,

169
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:31,760
just burying a person.

170
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,240
So I picked C20 for you.

171
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:39,600
Its initial setting time is about 1 to 3 hours.

172
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:40,800
That is to say,

173
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:42,600
in about 1 hour,

174
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,120
it will basically solidify.

175
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:47,400
And your coffin

176
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,500
will basically be formed.

177
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,160
But I'll give you a chance.

178
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,400
This tube

179
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:00,040
is for you to breathe.

180
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:03,640
As long as you remember where you put the stuff,

181
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:05,240
within 1 hour,

182
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:09,680
I can let you out.

183
00:15:11,680 --> 00:15:13,280
Thanks for the grand burial.

184
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:21,840
Hello, Mr. An.

185
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,320
I still have things to do.

186
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:28,520
Okay.

187
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:29,840
I got it.

188
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,800
Wait until the cement reaches his neck.

189
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:38,320
Give him the pipe.

190
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:49,440
Niu,

191
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:51,000
are we really going to kill him?

192
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,040
What do you think?

193
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:54,360
This is a human life.

194
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:55,160
If I...

195
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:06,600
Anyway, someone has to die here today.

196
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:09,000
It's either him,

197
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,320
or you.

198
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:15,860
You choose.

199
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,280
Do it.

200
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,120
You still have a chance.

201
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:54,800
Speak up.

202
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,240
Long.

203
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,200
Long, I give up.

204
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,640
I'll talk.

205
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:03,440
Stop.

206
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:06,920
Speak.

207
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,040
My legs are weak.

208
00:17:09,599 --> 00:17:11,119
My voice might be faint.

209
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:13,000
Long, come closer.

210
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,260
Closer, I'll tell you.

211
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,599
Trash.

212
00:17:17,319 --> 00:17:17,960
Speak.

213
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,000
A little closer.

214
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:24,720
Well,

215
00:17:25,319 --> 00:17:26,119
since

216
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:28,600
Daniu left,

217
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:31,960
you were already finished.

218
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:36,560
Buddy.

219
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:37,720
Don't make a move.

220
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:40,040
You didn't drink when I offered it earlier.

221
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:41,360
Now you are out of chances.

222
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:42,760
Pull yourself together.

223
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:44,440
It's time to hit the road.

224
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,000
I got it.

225
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,080
Give him the pipe.

226
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,660
Find me a pair of pants.

227
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,160
Baldy.

228
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:59,360
Take off your pants and give them to him.

229
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,760
You might be in a lot of trouble after I leave.

230
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:05,640
So I suggest you turn off your phone for six hours.

231
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:07,610
It is good for both of us.

232
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:11,280
Also, let me borrow your car.
